@prefix narr: <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Narrative_ContentCommentarySplit> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Narrative_ContentCommentarySplit> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ContentCommentarySplit> ;
    narr:childCount "5"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "b6a9d4d918338cfce5a392033500736cbdfb157d" ;
    narr:narration """The hub frames a structural distinction between two layers: [per-message primary source material](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ContentLayerPerMessage) transacted individually as it happens, and [authored reconciliation as commentary](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ReconciliationIsCommentaryLayer) written over a referent set after the fact. As of July 1 2026, the read model already honors this split — digests render primary-source grounding separately from a RECONCILED conclusion — but the write practice has not caught up, conflating the two by requiring memories to carry primary source content themselves. [Reconciliation as set transaction](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ReconciliationAsSetTransaction) develops the structural form: select a set of nodes, author something about them, surface which nodes the system is reasoning from — the legibility differentiator. [The unified write path](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_UnifiedWritePath) operationalizes this: web streams source live; dev submits a transport envelope the backend decomposes into individual source transactions plus reconciliation. By July 4, the principle had been extended outward: [the landing page IA](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_LandingPageEpistemicArchitecture) mirrors the product's own epistemics, applying the content/commentary split to the marketing surface itself.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ContentLayerPerMessage> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ReconciliationIsCommentaryLayer> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_LandingPageEpistemicArchitecture> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ReconciliationAsSetTransaction> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_UnifiedWritePath> ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "the per-message integrations that memories are then saved about" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ContentLayerPerMessage> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "The write practice has conflated them by requiring memories to include enough primary source content." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ReconciliationIsCommentaryLayer> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Disambiguate, never permission — the prompt rule." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ReconciliationAsSetTransaction> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "the memory is a transport envelope — the backend decomposes it into individual source transactions" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_UnifiedWritePath> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "The product's own epistemics become the page's IA." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_LandingPageEpistemicArchitecture> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The read model already separates the two layers; the write practice has not — a live asymmetry between what the system can render and what it can accept." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ReconciliationIsCommentaryLayer> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ContentLayerPerMessage> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Reconciliation is framed two ways that don't fully collapse: as authored epistemic commentary (a semantic act) and as a set transaction over graph nodes (a structural/mechanical act) — the tension between these framings is unresolved." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ReconciliationIsCommentaryLayer> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ReconciliationAsSetTransaction> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The landing page application (July 4) extends the principle to a marketing surface — an outlier use that is neither write-path engineering nor epistemic architecture, raising the question of how far the content/commentary split generalizes." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_LandingPageEpistemicArchitecture> ] ;
    narr:writer "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6" .
}